  <caption rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">There is an area of increased lucency in the inferior left lower lobe, with multiple dilated abnormal blood vessels. The area appears to be supplied predominantly by a large artery arising from the aorta just above the aortic hiatus. Drainage is to the left inferior pulmonary vein.</caption>
</owl:NamedIndividual>

