  <caption rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Contrast enhanced axial CT images through various levels of the chest demonstrate a unilateral right sided pleural effusion, with mildly enhancing circumferential, nodular, irregular thickened pleura, encasing the right hemithorax with a rindlike appearance. Additionally, there is focal nodularity of the mediastinal pleura. There is no significant adenopathy, nor evidence of a chest wall abnormality.</caption>
