<owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="#MPX1803_synpic28581">
  <rdf:type rdf:resource="#CT_Scan"/>
  <isScanOf rdf:resource="#case_MPX1803"/>
  <url rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">https://github.com/CHILab1/MedPix-2.0/blob/main/images/MPX1803_synpic28581.png</url>
  <caption rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Axial image of non-contrast CT shows mural mass on posterior wall of bladder just above the level of the prostate. Non-contrast CT performed just 10 days prior was repeated due to the bladder not being fully distended. Enlarged prostate contributed to difficulty of this case because mass effect produced an indentation in the same portion of the bladder wall. Also note atrophy of right abdominal rectus with irregular contour of the left abdominal rectus muscle which the patient first noted after thoracic surgery.</caption>
</owl:NamedIndividual>

