  <title rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Calcaneal Stress Fracture</title>
  <history rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">18 y/o male undergoing military boot camp who complains of right ankle pain upon jumping out of bed (approximately 6 ft high fall) and landing on ankle.</history>
  <exam rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Patient complained of point tenderness upon palpation of ankle. Rest of physical noncontributory.</exam>
  <finding rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Plain Films: No acute findingsMRI: Nondisplaced, compression type fracture of posterior calcaneus with extensive bone marrow and surrounding soft tissue edema.</finding>
  <differential_diagnosis rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">-Ankle Sprain-Stress Fracture-Arthritis-Tenosynovitis</differential_diagnosis>
