  <title rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Transmesenteric Internal Hernia</title>
  <history rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Abdominal pain. No known history of surgeries.</history>
  <exam rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">N/A</exam>
  <differential_diagnosis rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Malrotation with partial volvulusOmental herniaPartial sbo from adhensions</differential_diagnosis>
  <case_diagnosis rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Transmesenteric Internal Hernia</case_diagnosis>
  <diagnosis_by rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">no surgery yet</diagnosis_by>
  <discussion rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Most transmeseteric hernias are felt to be complications from surgery causing a defect in the mesentery. Interestingly, this patient has no known history of surgery.</discussion>
</owl:NamedIndividual>

