  <caption rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Axial and reformatted sagittal CT scans of the abdomen after oral and intraveous contrast show large extraluminal mass with areas of low-attenuation necrosis and hemorrhage and higher attenutation nodularity. On other images, the mass is adherent to the stomach, but not continuous with the gastric lumen and displaces surrounding viscera.</caption>
