  <caption rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">There is a well-circumscribed mildly T1 hyperintense and markedly T2 hypointense, nonenhancing mass, in the anterior-superior third ventricle. The hypointensity has been called the black hole effect of Colloid Cyst.</caption>
</owl:NamedIndividual>

