<owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="#case_MPX2139">
  <rdf:type rdf:resource="#Case"/>
  <hasScan rdf:resource="#MPX2139_synpic29035"/>
  <hasScan rdf:resource="#MPX2139_synpic29036"/>
  <hasScan rdf:resource="#MPX2139_synpic29037"/>
  <hasScan rdf:resource="#MPX2139_synpic29038"/>
  <hasPatient rdf:resource="#patient_0625"/>
  <title rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Myxopapillary ependymoma.</title>
  <history rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">19 year-old male with a six-month history of back pain and right leg weakness</history>
  <exam rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">N/A</exam>
  <finding rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">In the spinal canal, from approximately the mid body of T11 through the sacrum, is a large expansile intradural mass which is isointense to the cord on T1, hyperintense to the cord on T2 and avidly enhances with gadolinium albeit eterogeneously. Marked scalloping of the posterior vertebral bodies is noted most marked in the sacrum. This mass in the lumbar region extends into the neural foramina at all levels and expands the neural foramina at the lower segments with extension out of the right neural foramina at L5-S1. At the level of L4, there is a focal T2 bright lesion which may represent a small fatty element or small region of hemorrhage.</finding>
  <differential_diagnosis rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Myxopapillary ependymomaLarge nerve sheath tumorChordomaGaint cell tumorAneurysmal bone cyst</differential_diagnosis>
  <case_diagnosis rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Myxopapillary ependymoma.</case_diagnosis>
  <diagnosis_by rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Imaging characteristics and location - confirmed by pathology</diagnosis_by>
  <discussion rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Please see factoid.</discussion>
  <treatment_follow_up rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Surgical resection and post operative radiation planned.</treatment_follow_up>
</owl:NamedIndividual>

<owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="#MPX2139_synpic29035">
  <rdf:type rdf:resource="#MRI_Scan"/>
  <isScanOf rdf:resource="#case_MPX2139"/>
  <url rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">https://github.com/CHILab1/MedPix-2.0/blob/main/images/MPX2139_synpic29035.png</url>
  <caption rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">In the spinal canal, from approximately the mid body of T11 through the sacrum, is a large expansile intradural mass which is isointense to the cord on T1, hyperintense to the cord on T2 and avidly enhances with gadolinium albeit heterogeneous. Marked scalloping of the posterior vertebral bodies is noted at these levels which increased extending caudally, most marked in thesacrum. There is also canal expansion at L5 and into the sacrum.This mass in the lumbar region extends into the neural foramina at all levels and expands the neural foramina at the lower segments with likely extension out of the right neural foramina at L5-S1. At the level of L4, within the mass within the canal, there is a focal T2 bright lesion which may represent a small fatty element or small region of hemorrhage.</caption>
</owl:NamedIndividual>

