  <caption rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">MRI (T1W): Area of low signal intensity on the lateral aspect of the medial femoral condyle; surrounding this area within the femur is an area of very low signal intensity c/w fluid; there is also evidence of edema within the lesion, which may suggest an unstable fragment. There is evidence of mild cartilage thinning over the fragment but no tearing. The OCD is therefore nondisplaced.</caption>
</owl:NamedIndividual>

