  <url rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">https://github.com/CHILab1/MedPix-2.0/blob/main/images/MPX2428_synpic46480.png</url>
  <caption rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">An intradural extramedullary mass is seen at the T2 level measuring 1.2 cm AP x 1.1 cm transverse x 1.7 cm craniocaudad. This mass causes mild compression and leftward shift of the spinal cord. Subtle hyperintense T2 signal abnormality is noted within the mass, and uniformly enhances following gadolinium DTPA. There is a no dural tail. The spinal cord is normal in signal. No neural foraminal extension is seen.</caption>
</owl:NamedIndividual>

